# Fixture: fm7-filter-not-exists-vs-optional-rewrite
# Finding: Failure Mode 7 — FILTER NOT EXISTS is not equivalent to OPTIONAL/FILTER(!BOUND)
# Spec: SPARQL 1.1 §12.5 (FILTER NOT EXISTS formal semantics)
#
# Hypothesis: When the NOT EXISTS pattern shares ALL variables with the outer
# pattern, the OPTIONAL/FILTER(!BOUND(?x)) rewrite produces different semantics.
# FILTER NOT EXISTS { ?s ?p ?o } in the context of ?s ?p ?o . must return
# nothing (every solution has a matching triple, so NOT EXISTS is always false).
# The rewritten form OPTIONAL { ?s ?p ?o } FILTER (!BOUND(?o)) behaves
# differently because ?o was already bound before the OPTIONAL — the OPTIONAL
# never unbinds it.
#
# Divergence: Optimiser that rewrites FILTER NOT EXISTS as OPTIONAL/FILTER(!BOUND)
# returns results where the correct answer is empty, when inner and outer
# patterns share all variables.
# Grammar-level behaviour: parses successfully.

SELECT * WHERE {
  ?s ?p ?o .
  FILTER NOT EXISTS { ?s ?p ?o . }
}
